==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Oxyhydrogen
<hw>Ox`y*hy"dro*gen</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Oxy-</ets> <sd>(a)</sd> + <ets>hydrogen</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or consisting of, a mixture
of oxygen and hydrogen at over 5000⟦deg⟧ F.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Oxyhydrogen blowpipe</b></col>. <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<cd>See <er>Blowpipe</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Oxyhydrogen
microscope</b></col>, <cd>a form of microscope arranged so as to use the
light produced by burning lime or limestone under a current of
oxyhydrogen gas.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Oxyhydrogen light</ent>⟦br⟧
